title: [mlnode] Logging module, shut down function and the fixing of a bug about multi process training
body:
## Description
Logging module, shut down function and the fixing of a bug about multi process training
We have developed new functions for the mlnode module of IoTDB, which mainly includes the following three parts:

### Content
#### Logging module
Developed a logging module for mlnode, supporting standard function calls and localized log information for multi-process security
#### Shut down function
Completed the addition of the mlnode shutdown function, and implemented the direct shutdown of the mlnode main process based on the port number on the Linux system
#### Bug fixing
Fixed the issue involved in related work, which is that the original process pool does not support creating nums_ Issues with worker subprocesses

### Usage
#### Logging module
We provide 5 levels of functions including debug, info, warn, error, and the module can localize logs according to the log level. In subsequent development, we only need to use a form similar to calling the Python standard logging module to use it.
#### Stop function
Since our start function is designed in the form of pip package, our stop function is developed in a similar form. If user start the mlnode in a terminal, we can stop the node in another one with the command "mlnode stop".

Fix datanode stuck when meets disk error
body: ## Description When recover data region but meet disk error, the main thread of data node will stack at the following position. The errored data region didn't countdown the latch in WALRecoverManager. Therefore the main thread will aways wait for the WALRecoverManager to finish recover. After the fixing, the data node progress will exit when meets disk error. ## How to test 1. Generate some data files by execute insert statement and flush. ```sql insert into root.sg.d1(time,s1) values(1,2); flush; ``` 2. Stop data node, go to data dir `data/datanode/data/sequence/root.sg/1/0` 3. Create an empty temp file and set the temp file unchangeable to simulate the disk broken. DataNode will throw an IOException because of it. ``` touch 1695017988949-1-0-0.tsfile.resource.temp chflags uchg 1695017988949-1-0-0.tsfile.resource.temp ``` 4. Restart the data node.

[IOTDB-6157] Check timestamp precision when insert
body:
## Description

Some users may insert higher precision timestamps into an IoTDB with low timestamp precision. It may cause some stability problem, due to the time partition interval calculating with lower timestamp precision, a lot of unexpected time partition was created. Therefore, we hope to do the following checks when insert or load data.

When `timestamp_precision=ms`, check whether the inserting timestamp over 13 digits. If true, return error.
When `timestamp_precision=us`, check whether the inserting timestamp over 16 digits. If true, return error.
When `timestamp_precision=ns`, Long.maxValue is already 19 digits, no need to check.


## How to test

Insert or load data with higher precision by session, cli, restApi...

[IOTDB-6154] Pipe: better algorithm for hybrid mode to switch log/tsfile extraction in iotdb-extractor
body:
In this PR, I've made two improvements
1. HybridExtractor will first try to do extraction in log mode, and then choose log or tsfile mode to continue extracting, but if (leader data regions num * Wal size) > (maximum size of wal buffer) will cause OOM, so we need to use tsfile mode if the size exceeds the threshold.
2. PipeRealtimeDataRegionHybridExtractor don't need to use log mode until the historical extractor has consumed all the hitorical data.

title: [IOTDB-6149] Fix incorrect output of UDF with multiple inputs
body:
Issue: https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/IOTDB-6149
This pr fixed the incorrect initialization when calculating expressions with UDF which has multiple inputs.
How to reproduce:
1. Create a function with UDF that uses SlidingTimeWinodw AccessStrategy and takes multiple expressions as input.
2. Run a query using this function with multiple inputs like: select func(s1, s2) from root.sg
3. See if the ouput is correct.

Because UDFWindowIT#testSlidingTimeWindow did not check the cnt of expected rows, this bug could not be detected by the IT. I add the check in this PR now.
Also, In this pr, I removed some of the @Ignore annotions of UDFWindowIT since the exception handler of IT framework is finished as mentioned in the todo annotation.

```
+--------------+-----+--------+--------+--------+-----------+----+----------+--------+------------------+--------+
|    root.db.s1| null| root.db| BOOLEAN|     RLE|        LZ4|null|      null|    null|              null|    BASE|
|    root.db.s2| null| root.db| BOOLEAN|     RLE|        LZ4|null|      null|    null|              null|    BASE|
|root.db.d1.vs1| null| root.db| BOOLEAN|    null|       null|null|      null|    null|              null|    VIEW|
+--------------+-----+--------+--------+--------+-----------+----+----------+--------+------------------+--------+
Total line number = 3
It costs 0.030s
IoTDB> show view
+--------------+--------+--------+----+----------+--------+----------+
|    Timeseries|Database|DataType|Tags|Attributes|ViewType|    Source|
+--------------+--------+--------+----+----------+--------+----------+
|root.db.d1.vs1| root.db| BOOLEAN|null|      null|    VIEW|root.db.s1|
+--------------+--------+--------+----+----------+--------+----------+
Total line number = 1
It costs 0.016s
IoTDB> alter view root.db.d1.vs1 as select s2 from root.db
Msg: The statement is executed successfully.
IoTDB> alter view root.db.d1.vs1 as select s3 from root.db
Msg: 300: Columns in the query statement is empty. Please check your SQL.
IoTDB> alter view root.db.d1.vs1 as select s1,s2 from root.db
Msg: 300: The number of target paths (1) and sources (2) are miss matched! Please check your SQL. 
```

title: Permission mode refine final pr
body:
In this PR:

1. The functionality and code of the permission module have been modified to make it closer to the usage of relational databases. For more details, please refer to the official website.
2. The permission authorization logic for various modules has been adjusted, and more module functionalities will be subject to permission restrictions.
3. The internal code of the permission module has been adjusted. Due to the volume of permission data in the time-series database, permission data is maintained in memory and is only flushed in and out during snapshots, with consistency guaranteed by the consensus layer.

title: [To rel/1.2][IOTDB-6128] Pipe: supporting multiples device operation in flink-sql-iotdb-connector
Add template IT and fix
[auth].fix cache info.
body:
In this pr:
1. Add some IT for list operation and revoke operation. Insert and write will meet errors.
2.  Fix userresp info lost when the user's path privilege is null.
3. Fix List role operation. User can list roles that he has won.
4. Fix revoke operation. When we revoke privilege on a path, the database will revoke pathPri which can match our reputation. And add some UT for it.

title: [IOTDB-6143] Pipe: Support PipeConnector subtasks with the same parameters concurrently scheduling
body: * Support `connector.parrallel.task` attribute to specify the number of PipeConnectors to concurrently execute tasks.

title: [To rel/1.2] Pipe: include creation time in PipeProcessorSubtask#taskID to avoid task scheduling issues after 1000+ pipes' creating and dropping (#11078)
body:
How to reproduce:

* create 1000 devices and write some data
* create and start 1000 pipes, their patterns matching the devices
* drop all pipes
* delete all data on receiver side
* create and start the same pipes again
* execute queries on receiver side, and the data are NOT transferred

(cherry picked from commit ba46d351ed5bbdee65873b95bbf2687967bc6ba1)
